<section class="section section--compact" id="acct-speak-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure">
      <strong>You&rsquo;ll be speaking to our Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team &mdash; bookkeeping, QuickBooks, and advisory specialists, not CPAs.</strong> If your question is really a tax return, tax advice, or IRS representation, that&rsquo;s licensed CPA or enrolled-agent work &mdash; we&rsquo;ll tell you so plainly and help you coordinate a CPA or EA, often handing them books that are already clean and year-end-ready. We are also an independent firm: not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s official support. QuickBooks and Intuit are registered trademarks of Intuit Inc.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="acct-speak-byline">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="byline-block">
      <svg class="byline-block__mark" viewBox="0 0 64 64" role="img" aria-label="TechBrot"><rect width="64" height="64" rx="14" fill="#1A1915"></rect><g transform="translate(12.16 12.16) scale(0.62)" fill="#F5F3EC"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"></path><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"></rect></g></svg>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">Reviewed by a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor &middot; Online &amp; Desktop certified</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-speak-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">&ldquo;Speak to an accountant,&rdquo; honestly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p id="acct-speak-in-brief-text">When people search &ldquo;speak to an accountant,&rdquo; they usually mean one of two very different things &mdash; and the honest answer matters. Sometimes they need <em>bookkeeping</em>: someone to clean up the books, set up or fix QuickBooks, reconcile the accounts, produce financial statements they can trust, and advise on what the numbers mean. Other times they need <em>tax</em>: a return prepared and signed, tax advice they can rely on, or someone to deal with the IRS. The word &ldquo;accountant&rdquo; gets used for both, but the credentials are not the same.</p>
      <p>Our team are <strong>Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors</strong>. That is the first group of work &mdash; the operational accounting inside your books &mdash; and it&rsquo;s what we do well. We are <strong>not CPAs</strong>, so we do not prepare tax returns, give tax advice, or represent anyone before the IRS; that is licensed CPA or enrolled-agent work. We won&rsquo;t blur that line. If your call turns out to be a tax question, the most useful thing we can do is say so clearly and help you coordinate a CPA &mdash; usually with a clean, year-end-ready file already in hand.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-speak-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Speaking to our team, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-speak-causes">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What our team does</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What our ProAdvisor team can help with.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The operational accounting that keeps your numbers clean and decision-ready &mdash; everything here is ProAdvisor work, not tax-return preparation.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for c in causes %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ c.rank }}</p>
        <h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-speak-talk">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How to talk to a ProAdvisor.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Six steps, start to finish. Most calls only take the first three &mdash; and if it turns out you need a CPA, we&rsquo;ll tell you on the way through.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="fix-steps">
      {%- for s in fixSteps %}
      <li>
        <span class="n">{{ loop.index }}</span>
        <div><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-speak-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">When it&rsquo;s a CPA&rsquo;s job</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">When you need a CPA instead (and how we coordinate).</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for p in proSignals %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-speak-breakout">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="call-breakout">
      <div>
        <p class="call-breakout__title">Ready to talk, or just want a read on the books?</p>
        <p class="call-breakout__sub">The discovery call is free &mdash; you reach our Certified ProAdvisor team, and we&rsquo;re straight about whether it&rsquo;s our work or a CPA&rsquo;s. Prefer to see the state of the file first? A free QuickBooks file review gives you a clear answer with no obligation. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, not a CPA firm.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/contact/?intent=accounting">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-speak-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who you reach</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor takes the call &mdash; and routes you honestly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>When you reach out, you&rsquo;re talking to a member of our Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team &mdash; the people who actually do the bookkeeping, QuickBooks, reconciliation, financial-statement, and advisory work, with active Online and Desktop certifications. They&rsquo;ll listen, work out what you really need, and give you a fixed-fee written scope before any work begins. What they won&rsquo;t do is pretend to be a CPA: if the call is about a tax return, tax advice, or the IRS, they&rsquo;ll say so and help you coordinate a CPA or enrolled agent. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-speak-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
